cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision and deep learning techniques for classification, detection, and counting of cars from overhead images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of contextual information, which can be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The dataset creation and management can be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which can be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
